# `Queue` and `Deque`

## FIFO and double-ended

- **`Queue`** — first in, first out
- **`Deque`** — add/remove either end → also a **stack**

## Use `ArrayDeque`

```java
Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
stack.push(1); stack.push(2);
stack.pop();   // 2   (LIFO)

Queue<String> q = new ArrayDeque<>();
q.offer("first"); q.offer("second");
q.poll();      // "first"   (FIFO)
```

## Why not the alternatives

- Faster than `LinkedList` for both patterns; avoid legacy synchronised `Stack`
